        <title>Something&#x27;s Missing (WIP)</title>
        <author>
            <name>Craig Macnaughton</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://www.craigmacnaughton.com/somethings-missing.html"/>
        <id>https://www.craigmacnaughton.com/somethings-missing.html</id>

        <updated>2022-06-27T17:49:24-04:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    How do you cope when you're feeling all alone? Stuff yourself with rollercoasters, junk food or video games? Surround yourself&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                <p>How do you cope when you're feeling all alone? Stuff yourself with rollercoasters, junk food or video games? Surround yourself with friends? A quirky story about loneliness, SOMETHING'S MISSING shows how sometimes it's OK to be all by yourself.</p>
<p>SOMETHING'S MISSING (WC 328) was born of my own feelings of loneliness as a stay-at-home parent and someone who struggles with depression. I wanted to let my kids know that it's OK to be lonely sometimes, but in a fun, engaging way full of "what ifs" and silliness.</p>
<p>Download <a href="https://www.craigmacnaughton.com/Somethings-Missing-Thumbnails-Macnaughton.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dummy Thumbnails (PDF)</a></p>
